The evidence with the title 'Dirty air from global trade kills at home, abroad, study contends ' says Mar 29, 2017  ... Each year , more than 750000 people die prematurely from dirty air generated by making goods in one location that will be sold elsewhere , study says.  ... China and India also have pollution that travels elsewhere and kills between 65,000 and 75,000 people in other countries , the study said . 
